From: Scott Wood <scottwood@freescale.com>
Date: Tue, 3 Feb 2015 19:22:08 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 027/452] usb: dwc3: Don't assume dev has a parent

The dma mask is currently defaulting to 0xffffffff.  I don't know if
that's as large as this device can do, but it beats a NULL pointer
dereference.

Signed-off-by: Scott Wood <scottwood@freescale.com>
Change-Id: Icd954a5b21fae8cfa505185c2bf17d8fd3392940
Reviewed-on: http://git.am.freescale.net:8181/30110
Tested-by: Review Code-CDREVIEW <CDREVIEW@freescale.com>
Reviewed-by: Bhupesh Sharma <bhupesh.sharma@freescale.com>
Tested-by: Bhupesh Sharma <bhupesh.sharma@freescale.com>
(cherry picked from commit 66ca09b1d8c37cb3d3d5c4d0d2a1f1797cd5dc98)
Signed-off-by: Stuart Yoder <stuart.yoder@freescale.com>
[Xulin: Original patch taken from FSL LS2085 SDK EAR6.0,
LS2085A-SDK-SOURCE-20160304-yocto.iso]
Signed-off-by: Xulin Sun <xulin.sun@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/usb/dwc3/core.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/dwc3/core.c b/drivers/usb/dwc3/core.c
index 1f79708..3669fd8 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/dwc3/core.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/dwc3/core.c
@@ -984,7 +984,7 @@ static int dwc3_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 
 	spin_lock_init(&dwc->lock);
 
-	if (!dev->dma_mask) {
+	if (!dev->dma_mask && dev->parent) {	
 		dev->dma_mask = dev->parent->dma_mask;
 		dev->dma_parms = dev->parent->dma_parms;
 		dma_set_coherent_mask(dev, dev->parent->coherent_dma_mask);
